    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-gray-500 mb-6">WHY ARE WE DOING THIS?</p>

    <p class="mb-4">"Off" and "leave it" are safety commands. Whether it's jumping on a fragile elderly person, eating chocolate left on the counter, or sniffing something toxic at the park, these commands give you a way to interrupt potentially dangerous behaviors.</p>

    <p>They also teach impulse control. A dog who can leave a piece of cheese on the ground when you say so is a dog who's learning to control their impulses. This skill transfers to other areas - less reactivity to dogs, better door manners, more patience when waiting for meals.</p>
